Cape Town - Black Friday has hit South Africa, causing chaos inside - and outside - stores. Some stores have opened at midnight, prompting eager consumers to come out in their numbers to take advantage of the sales. In a bid to not lose their space in the queue, people camped out and slept in the queues. For those hoping to avoid the packed shops, numerous online shopping sites have reportedly crashed, causing outrage among those who were eager to skip the lines. Businesses have taken to social media to advertise their "not-to-be-missed" specials and people used social media to share images and videos of the Black Friday hype.       To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
